772
00:55:19,320 --> 00:55:22,680
I know, I know, you have plenty on
your plates already---

773
00:55:22,730 --> 00:55:25,450
but this is a request from the top.

774
00:55:28,300 --> 00:55:29,800
The very top.

775
00:55:30,750 --> 00:55:32,250
Thank you.

776
00:55:39,250 --> 00:55:41,260
This is complete crap, man.

777
00:55:41,310 --> 00:55:44,460
What is this, huh? Are we some sort
of circus act now?

778
00:55:44,510 --> 00:55:46,310
We didn't talk about shit like this.

779
00:55:46,360 --> 00:55:49,340
They expect us to play our best,
to give our bloody all,

780
00:55:49,390 --> 00:55:51,460
then they add to our bloody
workload...

781
00:55:51,510 --> 00:55:52,700
He's right.

782
00:55:52,750 --> 00:55:55,250
What do you think about this, Chester?

783
00:55:57,620 --> 00:56:00,500
I try not to think. 'Cause it interferes
with my rugby.

784
00:56:00,550 --> 00:56:02,750
See! Now there's a rugby player.

785
00:56:03,090 --> 00:56:04,720
Talk to them, cappie.

786
00:56:04,770 --> 00:56:07,160
You gotta make them understand
we just don't have the time for this.

787
00:56:07,210 --> 00:56:08,780
Ja.

788
00:56:08,950 --> 00:56:10,470
I'm not going to talk to them.

789
00:56:10,520 --> 00:56:12,020
Why not?

790
00:56:13,090 --> 00:56:16,650
We've become more then just a rugby
team.

791
00:56:17,700 --> 00:56:20,100
And we might as well get used to it.

792
00:56:21,840 --> 00:56:24,190
Is this you speaking, or Mandela?

793
00:56:24,610 --> 00:56:25,980
<i>Yeah, exactly, huh?</i>

794
00:56:26,030 --> 00:56:28,080
You know me better than that.

795
00:56:33,600 --> 00:56:35,350
You know, times change.

796
00:56:37,920 --> 00:56:40,070
And we need to change as well.

797
00:56:40,860 --> 00:56:42,670
<i>Oh, that's great.</i>

798
00:57:16,690 --> 00:57:18,000
Shit.

799
00:57:18,100 --> 00:57:19,100
Ja.

800
00:57:19,160 --> 00:57:21,110
I'm glad I don't live here.

801
00:57:40,810 --> 00:57:43,910
Don't forget, we've got cameras on
us at all times.

802
00:57:43,980 --> 00:57:45,530
What a bloody joke.

803
00:57:49,790 --> 00:57:52,690
"CHESTER CHESTER CHESTER"

804
00:58:06,810 --> 00:58:08,910
Chester--- I reckon you're up.

805
00:58:08,960 --> 00:58:11,450
- What am I supposed to do?
- What you do best.

806
00:58:11,500 --> 00:58:13,000
Let rip.

807
00:58:13,800 --> 00:58:15,600
Who wants to play rugby?

808
00:58:30,070 --> 00:58:31,600
Who here knows the first rule of
rugby?

809
00:58:31,650 --> 00:58:32,490
Me.

810
00:58:32,540 --> 00:58:36,340
- What is it? - You hit another
players when the Raf isn't looking!

811
00:58:36,390 --> 00:58:38,380
No, no, no. The first rule of rugby

812
00:58:38,430 --> 00:58:41,550
is you can only pass the ball
backwards or sideways.

813
00:58:41,600 --> 00:58:43,180
All right? Do we practise that?

814
00:58:43,230 --> 00:58:45,380
- "Ja"
- All right. Form a line.

815
00:58:45,690 --> 00:58:47,640
Let's go, boys. Here we go.

816
00:58:49,370 --> 00:58:50,470
Get ready.

817
00:58:54,050 --> 00:58:55,750
Keep your hands up.

818
00:58:55,850 --> 00:58:57,040
Okay.

819
00:59:02,030 --> 00:59:03,700
Like this, like this.

820
00:59:03,830 --> 00:59:06,030
I'm here so I make it like this.

821
00:59:07,630 --> 00:59:09,610
Now, you run.

822
00:59:13,610 --> 00:59:15,110
There you go.

823
00:59:16,000 --> 00:59:17,420
...and then catch it. Right.

824
00:59:17,470 --> 00:59:19,440
So, I want you in groups of three,
okay?

825
00:59:19,490 --> 00:59:21,460
All right. One, two, three!

826
01:00:21,520 --> 01:00:24,360
...and in addition to the nationwide
PR campaign,

827
01:00:24,410 --> 01:00:26,880
we propose that all retail outlets
charge

828
01:00:26,930 --> 01:00:29,080
a nominal fee for plastic bags.

829
01:00:29,290 --> 01:00:32,540
We believe that this will generate---
