just landed. - Okay. - Thank you.

840
01:01:29,070 --> 01:01:32,300
<i>The green and gold have just one week to
put the finishing touches</i>

841
01:01:32,350 --> 01:01:34,570
<i>to their gruelling training program</i>

842
01:01:34,620 --> 01:01:37,140
and I, for one, must admit to being

843
01:01:37,370 --> 01:01:39,070
cautiously optimistic.

844
01:01:39,280 --> 01:01:43,580
I say cautiously, because in my
humble opinion

845
01:01:43,910 --> 01:01:48,090
this Springbok team has been
over-practised on the field,

846
01:01:48,280 --> 01:01:50,180
and over-committed off it.

847
01:01:50,790 --> 01:01:53,720
<i>Which makes beating a powerhouse
Australian side</i>

848
01:01:53,770 --> 01:01:56,460
<i>in next week's Cup opener a tall
order,</i>

849
01:01:56,590 --> 01:01:59,400
<i>especially as this is
an inexperienced team</i>

850
01:01:59,580 --> 01:02:02,580
<i>with a history of coming up short in
big matches.</i>

851
01:02:02,870 --> 01:02:05,180
<i>This is Johan de Villiers, Live in
Cape Town,</i>

852
01:02:05,230 --> 01:02:07,980
<i>returning you to the studio in
Johannesburg.</i>

853
01:02:08,240 --> 01:02:09,560
<i>Thanks Johan. The update---</i>

854
01:02:09,610 --> 01:02:11,910
Around the world--- objectively---

855
01:02:12,970 --> 01:02:16,370
what are they saying about our
chances to beat Australia?

856
01:02:16,520 --> 01:02:18,370
Everyone thinks they'll beat us.

857
01:02:18,420 --> 01:02:22,150
And if they do, we'll have to go
through England and the All Blacks

858
01:02:22,200 --> 01:02:24,050
just to get to the Final.

859
01:02:24,420 --> 01:02:28,170
So it is very important that we beat
Australia.

860
01:02:30,960 --> 01:02:32,460
Thank you.

861
01:02:44,280 --> 01:02:49,160
Madiba, the Cabinet Ministers are here
to brief you on the trip to Taiwan.

862
01:02:49,590 --> 01:02:50,610
Oh, yes.

863
01:02:50,670 --> 01:02:53,120
- I'll be right out.
- Thank you, sir.

864
01:03:01,680 --> 01:03:06,040
¶ Matters not the circumstance ¶

865
01:03:07,210 --> 01:03:11,700
¶ We rise above, take a chance ¶

866
01:03:12,080 --> 01:03:14,475
¶ I thank whatever ¶

867
01:03:14,830 --> 01:03:16,920
¶ Whatever gods may be ¶

868
01:03:19,300 --> 01:03:23,070
¶ 9,000 days were set aside¶

869
01:03:24,740 --> 01:03:28,690
¶ 9,000 days of destiny ¶

870
01:03:30,150 --> 01:03:32,650
¶ 9,000 days to thank gods ¶

871
01:03:32,920 --> 01:03:36,600
¶ Wherever they may be ¶

872
01:03:37,620 --> 01:03:39,100
One week, boys.

873
01:03:49,160 --> 01:03:53,460
We want snipers on top of the stadium
and the surrounding buildings here.

874
01:03:53,570 --> 01:03:54,750
No problem.

875
01:03:54,800 --> 01:03:57,830
We want those two approaches
completely sanitized.

876
01:03:57,880 --> 01:03:58,920
Two approaches?

877
01:03:58,970 --> 01:04:02,740
We're not going to decide which way
he comes in until the very last moment.

878
01:04:02,790 --> 01:04:07,210
We want uniforms, plain clothes,
sharp-shooters...

879
01:04:07,830 --> 01:04:09,330
And sniffer dogs.

880
01:04:09,610 --> 01:04:11,580
And if you need more men,
we have an army unit for you

881
01:04:11,630 --> 01:04:13,480
on standby at Silvermine.

882
01:04:13,630 --> 01:04:16,390
We're not going to take chances,
gentlemen.

883
01:04:16,440 --> 01:04:18,840
The President's going to be exposed.

884
01:04:19,850 --> 01:04:21,310
Much too exposed.

885
01:04:32,450 --> 01:04:33,930
Brenda...

886
01:04:35,350 --> 01:04:37,150
...I have been studying.

887
01:04:37,530 --> 01:04:40,310
For the summit in Taiwan? Good.

888
01:04:41,080 --> 01:04:43,130
No. Not exactly.

889
01:04:44,060 --> 01:04:45,530
Test me.

890
01:04:46,020 --> 01:04:48,020
They look like thugs.

891
01:04:48,980 --> 01:04:50,600
Block out their names.

892
01:04:50,650 --> 01:04:53,050
See if I can recognize them.

893
01:04:58,210 --> 01:04:59,780
Andre Joubert.

894
01:05:00,280 --> 01:05:01,780
Gavin Johnson.

895
01:05:02,660 --> 01:05:04,300
Did I get them right?

896
01:05:04,350 --> 01:05:05,850
Yes, Madiba.

897
01:05:06,790 --> 01:05:09,590
That's the way I used to study in
law school.

898
01:05:10,550 --> 01:05:11,850
Unfortunately,

899
01:05:12,510 --> 01:05:14,910
Chester is far too easy to identify.

900
01:05:15,500 --> 01:05:17,650
But that will change.

901
01:05:18,680 --> 01:05:19,970
It must.

902
01:05:27,780 --> 01:05:29,300
- Go.
- Go. Go. Go.

903
01:05:33,860 --> 01:05:35,810
Team meeting. After dinner.

904
01:05:37,100 --> 01:05:38,700
C'mon, Springboks!

905
01:05:49,150 --> 01:05:50,750
Round. Gather round.

906
01:05:53,160 --> 01:05:54,740
- Pass it away.
- What's this Francois? Homework?

907
01:05:54,790 --> 01:05:56,290
Ja, ja.

908
01:05:56,440 --> 01:05:58,590
Make sure everyone has got one.

909
01:06:01,150 --> 01:06:02,200
What is this?

910
01:06:02,250 --> 01:06:04,170
We need to learn this song.

911
01:06:04,220 --> 01:06:05,650
We can't just mouth the words
anymore.

912
01:06:05,700 --> 01:06:08,100
Nobody cares, as long as we're
winning the matches.

913
01:06:08,150 --> 01:06:10,100
You're wrong. They do care.

914
01:06:10,310 --> 01:06:12,560
It's their bloody song, not ours.

915
01:06:12,810 --> 01:06:14,540
Flippin' terrorist song, man.

916
01:06:14,590 --> 01:06:16,460
Yeah, they used to arrest you for
singing it.

917
01:06:16,510 --> 01:06:18,540
Right, and now it's one of our
anthems.

918
01:06:18,590 --> 01:06:21,340
I can't even read it or pronounce
the words.

919
01:06:24,030 --> 01:06:26,080
All right, guys. It's optional.

920
01:06:26,130 --> 01:06:27,880
Take it if you want to.

921
01:06:35,920 --> 01:06:37,920
It means "God Bless Africa".

922
01:06:40,440 --> 01:06:43,330
Which you have to admit, we could
use.

923
01:06:55,550 --> 01:06:59,730
Tell us, Mr. President, have you
always been a rugby fan?

924
01:07:01,430 --> 01:07:06,150
People do not realize that I played
rugby myself,

925
01:07:06,500 --> 01:07:08,800
when I was a student at Fort Hare.

926
01:07:09,560 --> 01:07:11,360
It is a very rough game.

927
01:07:11,710 --> 01:07:13,710
Almost as rough as politics.

928
01:07:15,780 --> 01:07:18,290
How do you think the Springboks
will do?

929
01:07:18,340 --> 01:07:20,490
I think they will do very well.

930
01:07:20,880 --> 01:07:23,480
Their level of commitment is tremendous.

931
01:07:24,120 --> 01:07:27,980
Now, it's been said that you used to
support any team

932
01:07:28,240 --> 01:07:30,310
that played against the Springboks.

933
01:07:30,360 --> 01:07:33,160
Yes, well, obviously, that is no
longer true.

934
01:07:33,580 --> 01:07:36,230
I am one hundred percent behind our
boys.

935
01:07:36,820 --> 01:07:41,390
After all, if I cannot change
when circumstances demand it,

936
01:07:42,080 --> 01:07:44,400
how can I expect others to?

937
01:07:46,100 --> 01:07:48,310
¶ And it's not just a game ¶

938
01:07:48,500 --> 01:07:50,810
¶ You can't throw me away ¶

939
01:07:51,400 --> 01:07:54,860
¶ I put all I had on the line ¶

940
01:07:55,600 --> 01:07:57,840
¶ And I give and you take ¶

941
01:07:57,970 --> 01:08:00,740
¶ And I played the high stakes ¶

942
01:08:00,970 --> 01:08:02,660
¶ I've won and I've lost ¶

943
01:08:02,710 --> 01:08:04,840
¶ But, I'm fine ¶

944
01:08:05,060 --> 01:08:09,420
¶ Hear me say I'll wise up 'til the end ¶

945
01:08:09,820 --> 01:08:14,440
¶ Hear me say I'll stand up for my
friends ¶

946
01:08:14,560 --> 01:08:16,880
¶ And I crash to the ground ¶

947
01:08:16,950 --> 01:08:19,800
¶ And it's just my own sound ¶

948
01:08:20,040 --> 01:08:23,790
¶ I drop in the blink of an eye ¶

949
01:08:25,700 --> 01:08:30,720
¶ I'm colorblind ¶

950
01:08:38,000 --> 01:08:40,090
- Francois.
- Welcome Mr. President.

951
01:08:40,140 --> 01:08:41,640
Gentlemen...

952
01:08:41,920 --> 01:08:44,370
forgive me for interrupting your
work

953
01:08:44,520 --> 01:08:47,160
the day before such an important
match,

954
01:08:47,210 --> 01:08:51,450
but I just wanted to come and wish
you good luck, in person.

955
01:08:52,420 --> 01:08:55,810
Sometimes, very seldom, as President,

956
01:08:55,900 --> 01:08:58,050
I am allowed to do what I want.

957
01:08:59,590 --> 01:09:01,140
Mr. President, this is---

958
01:09:01,190 --> 01:09:03,380
Oh, I know, who this is.

959
01:09:03,940 --> 01:09:06,690
- Andre, good luck.
- Pleased to meet you. Thank you, sir.

960
01:09:06,740 --> 01:09:08,640
Brendan, good luck to you.

961
01:09:09,560 --> 01:09:11,790
- Kevin, good luck.
- Thank you.

962
01:09:12,040 --> 01:09:13,290
- James.
- Mr. President.

963
01:09:13,340 --> 01:09:14,450
- Good luck.
- Thank you.

964
01:09:14,500 --> 01:09:15,890
- Japie
- Thank you, sir.

965
01:09:15,940 --> 01:09:17,440
Good luck.

966
01:09:17,560 --> 01:09:19,460
Did you ever imagine this?

967
01:09:19,530 --> 01:09:20,550
Good luck.

968
01:09:20,600 --> 01:09:22,100
How could I?

969
01:09:23,090 --> 01:09:25,510
- Thank you. Good luck.
- Mr. President.

970
01:09:25,560 --> 01:09:27,360
- Good luck.
- Thank you.

971
01:09:27,700 --> 01:09:29,700
Good luck to you.

972
01:09:29,920 --> 01:09:31,610
Good luck.

973
01:09:31,660 --> 01:09:33,160
Good luck, son.

974
01:09:33,440 --> 01:09:35,080
Good luck. Hennie...

975
01:09:35,130 --> 01:09:36,460
- ...Good luck.
- Thank you.

976
01:09:36,510 --> 01:09:40,930
But where is Chester?

977
01:09:42,670 --> 01:09:47,420
He's injured, sir. His hamstring.
We're trying to keep it quiet.

978
01:09:48,280 --> 01:09:51,670
Well, will he be out for the entire
tournament?

979
01:09:53,310 --> 01:09:55,350
With hamstrings, who knows?

980
01:09:56,770 --> 01:09:58,270
We'll miss him.

981
01:09:58,720 --> 01:10:00,920
The whole country will miss him.

982
01:10:02,170 --> 01:10:04,020
- Well, gentlemen...
- Mr. President, sir---

983
01:10:04,070 --> 01:10:06,720
- Yes, Hennie.
- This is for you. From us.

984
01:10:13,530 --> 01:10:16,690
I'm honored, gentlemen. Truly
honored.

985
01:10:18,290 --> 01:10:23,700
And you must know that your country
supports you, completely.

986
01:10:25,460 --> 01:10:28,090
- Good luck to you all.
- "Thank you, sir"

987
01:10:28,140 --> 01:10:29,890
Francois, walk with me.

988
01:10:32,980 --> 01:10:35,040
I have something for you.

989
01:10:38,830 --> 01:10:41,200
It has helped me through the years.

990
01:10:41,890 --> 01:10:43,540
I hope, it helps you.

991
01:10:44,540 --> 01:10:46,390
Thank you, Mr. President.

992
01:10:46,520 --> 01:10:48,020
Thank you.

993
01:10:59,460 --> 01:11:01,430
It's time for bed, Tata.

994
01:11:03,130 --> 01:11:05,130
I'm going to stay up awhile.

995
01:11:05,490 --> 01:11:07,200
The country is excited tonight.

996
01:11:07,250 --> 01:11:09,600
You need to sleep. The doctor said.

997
01:11:11,120 --> 01:11:13,520
The doctor has no sense of occasion.

998
01:11:21,120 --> 01:11:24,560
<i>...and the good result here today...</i>

999
01:11:26,870 --> 01:11:29,390
<i>...black and gold...</i>

1000
01:11:35,010 --> 01:11:36,510
