1005
01:12:04,680 --> 01:12:06,870
Nerine... No, I can't... I can't...

1006
01:12:06,920 --> 01:12:08,810
- Come on, Francois. It's been weeks.
-  I can't. I need to be really angry.

1007
01:12:08,860 --> 01:12:11,810
I know, it's working. I need to be
angry tomorrow.

1008
01:12:11,860 --> 01:12:13,860
- What is this?
- A poem.

1009
01:12:14,980 --> 01:12:18,190
From President. - How does a poem
help you play rugby?

1010
01:12:18,240 --> 01:12:20,890
The same way your visit does.
Inspiration.

1011
01:12:57,070 --> 01:12:59,120
All right. Come on. With you.

1012
01:13:06,810 --> 01:13:08,810
- What happened?
- We scored.

1013
01:13:17,020 --> 01:13:18,790
Come on.

1014
01:14:02,060 --> 01:14:03,560
Go!

1015
01:14:10,250 --> 01:14:11,600
We won.

1016
01:14:11,820 --> 01:14:13,320
We did?

1017
01:14:38,920 --> 01:14:41,340
- Very good.
- That was beautiful, Tata.

1018
01:14:41,390 --> 01:14:44,640
- What do you say to this?
- Well. That was fantastic!

1019
01:15:05,420 --> 01:15:07,170
You must be very happy!

1020
01:15:07,890 --> 01:15:11,890
Any man would be happy to be dancing
with a beautiful lady like you.

1021
01:15:13,210 --> 01:15:15,580
Mr. President, you're exaggerating.

1022
01:15:15,630 --> 01:15:17,130
Not at all.

1023
01:15:17,270 --> 01:15:21,290
My father was a Xhosa,
so he was a polygamist.

