01:15:22,150 --> 01:15:23,930
As you know, I am not.

1025
01:15:25,620 --> 01:15:29,150
But when I look at you...
I envy my father.

1026
01:16:11,830 --> 01:16:15,300
"Say, one, two, three, four! Hey!"

1027
01:16:22,530 --> 01:16:24,500
Coach's run, six a.m.

1028
01:16:24,660 --> 01:16:26,410
- What?
- Pass it on.

1029
01:16:28,880 --> 01:16:31,080
Coach's run, six a.m.

1030
01:16:31,960 --> 01:16:33,140
Six.

1031
01:16:33,240 --> 01:16:34,990
Drink up.

1032
01:16:35,750 --> 01:16:39,070
Joe. Coach's run, six, six a.m.

1033
01:17:17,540 --> 01:17:21,140
Hey, guys. I hope you're not going
to be this slow next week.

1034
01:17:21,390 --> 01:17:23,800
- Hi. - I like to see you.
- Cappie? What's going on?

1035
01:17:23,850 --> 01:17:25,370
A change of pace. Come.

1036
01:17:25,420 --> 01:17:27,720
- Bloody boy!
- There you go. Good.

1037
01:17:27,810 --> 01:17:28,970
Come.

1038
01:17:29,650 --> 01:17:31,470
<i>Bye-bye.</i>

1039
01:18:14,480 --> 01:18:16,940
That's what they used to do, smuggle
gravel in from the yard

1040
01:18:16,990 --> 01:18:19,680
throw it across the floor so they
could hear the wardens come in

1041
01:18:19,730 --> 01:18:21,030
Oh, wow.

1042
01:18:22,900 --> 01:18:26,050
- Can we see the President's cell?
- Yes, of course.

1043
01:18:27,240 --> 01:18:29,140
Wow. Can you believe this?

1044
01:18:31,590 --> 01:18:33,940
Now, the number on the door...

1045
01:18:34,040 --> 01:18:39,310
46664 means, he was the 466th prisoner
to be intend here in 1964.

1046
01:18:40,850 --> 01:18:43,300
We've done it up just the way it was.

1047
01:18:51,030 --> 01:18:52,530
Come with me.

1048
01:19:30,150 --> 01:19:32,450
"Out of the night that covers me,"

1049
01:19:33,920 --> 01:19:36,640
"Black as the pit from pole to pole,"

1050
01:19:37,850 --> 01:19:40,280
"I thank whatever gods may be"

1051
01:19:41,630 --> 01:19:44,170
" For my unconquerable soul."

1052
01:19:45,000 --> 01:19:47,800
"In the fell clutch of circumstance"

1053
01:19:49,320 --> 01:19:52,330
"I have not winced nor cried aloud."

1054
01:19:54,000 --> 01:19:57,020
"Under the bludgeonings of chance"

1055
01:19:57,170 --> 01:20:00,900
"My head is bloody, but unbow'd."

1056
01:20:02,790 --> 01:20:05,940
"Beyond this place of wrath and tears"

1057
01:20:06,780 --> 01:20:09,430
"Looms but the Horror of the shade,"

1058
01:20:14,980 --> 01:20:18,010
"And yet the menace of the years"

1059
01:20:18,060 --> 01:20:24,250
"Finds and shall find me unafraid."

1060
01:20:26,880 --> 01:20:29,330
"It matters not how strait the gate,"

1061
01:20:30,870 --> 01:20:33,550
"How charged with punishment the scroll,"

1062
01:20:34,610 --> 01:20:37,170
"I am the master of my fate:"

1063
01:20:39,250 --> 01:20:41,610
"I am the captain of my soul."

1064
01:20:56,520 --> 01:20:57,980
Look at that.

1065
01:21:18,460 --> 01:21:20,040
Tata? Madiba?

1066
01:21:20,210 --> 01:21:21,260
Sir?

1067
01:21:27,560 --> 01:21:28,860
What happened?

1068
01:21:28,920 --> 01:21:32,580
It's simple exhaustion, but it'll lead
to worse if it's not treated.

1069
01:21:32,630 --> 01:21:34,480
He needs a complete rest.

1070
01:21:34,620 --> 01:21:38,660
And I don't mean just simply shifting
the affairs of state to his bedroom.

1071
01:21:38,710 --> 01:21:41,250
No phone calls, no visitors,
no meetings. No politics.

1072
01:21:41,300 --> 01:21:43,320
You know him. He won't do that.

1073
01:21:43,370 --> 01:21:45,460
Then I'm going to put him into
hospital. In isolation.

1074
01:21:45,510 --> 01:21:48,740
No. Not yet. I'll threaten him with
hospital if he doesn't behave.

1075
01:21:48,790 --> 01:21:50,040
I'll cancel everything.

1076
01:21:50,090 --> 01:21:53,490
And I'll come back tonight to make
sure he's not waking.

1077
01:21:56,410 --> 01:21:59,060
Don't cancel the trip to Taiwan.
Not yet.

1078
01:22:04,540 --> 01:22:06,090
What was that mean?

1079
01:22:16,890 --> 01:22:18,360
Chester's back.

1080
01:23:32,500 --> 01:23:35,540
<i>All right. All right. That's enough.
All right.</i>

1081
01:24:09,840 --> 01:24:12,650
Madiba, this is the delegation---

1082
01:24:12,950 --> 01:24:14,740
I know who this is.

1083
01:24:15,620 --> 01:24:16,700
Welcome.

1084
01:24:16,750 --> 01:24:19,910
Thank you for coming so far to see me.
- Thank you. How do you do?

1085
01:24:19,960 --> 01:24:21,960
- I'm fine. Welcome.
- Thank you very much.

1086
01:24:22,010 --> 01:24:25,450
<i>Ladies and gentlemen please
apologize. The game is delayed.</i>

1087
01:24:25,500 --> 01:24:29,160
<i>...in the semifinals, South Africa
against France...</i>

1088
01:24:33,290 --> 01:24:36,140
- This is it. Let's go.
- All right. Go.

1089
01:25:24,950 --> 01:25:27,390
<i>...International business alliances.</i>

1090
01:25:27,300 --> 01:25:30,750
<i>Strong industries have developed in
shipping and computers</i>

1091
01:25:30,890 --> 01:25:32,340
<i>Our information...</i>

1092
01:25:32,390 --> 01:25:33,890
Please, excuse me.

1093
01:25:34,090 --> 01:25:36,190
<i>Yes, Mr. President, of course.</i>

1094
01:25:39,250 --> 01:25:42,450
<i>Gentlemen, let us continue  in ten
minutes...</i>

1095
01:25:45,580 --> 01:25:47,380
This is good. Very good!

1096
01:25:48,150 --> 01:25:50,200
So, who is our next opponent?

1097
01:25:50,370 --> 01:25:53,670
The All Blacks play England tomorrow.
Then, we'll know.

1098
01:25:53,760 --> 01:25:54,860
I see.

1099
01:25:55,050 --> 01:25:59,050
You will make sure that my schedule
is free for the entire match.

1100
01:25:59,250 --> 01:26:00,770
Oh, yes, Tata.

1101
01:26:00,900 --> 01:26:03,460
This is good. This is very good.

1102
01:26:22,100 --> 01:26:25,750
<i>...black team mates come to
congratulate big fella yet again.</i>

1103
01:26:26,330 --> 01:26:28,760
<i>Lomu is becoming one of the most
intimidating...</i>

1104
01:26:28,810 --> 01:26:31,710
Why don't we do a little work while
we're here.

1105
01:26:33,550 --> 01:26:35,470
Just enjoy the rugby.

1106
01:26:35,850 --> 01:26:38,460
<i>...World Cup semifinal against
England.</i>

1107
01:26:41,430 --> 01:26:43,200
So, let me understand this.

1108
01:26:43,250 --> 01:26:46,110
The All Blacks are killing a team
that thrashed us last year?

1109
01:26:46,160 --> 01:26:47,960
Thanks for reminding me.

1110
01:26:52,900 --> 01:26:54,400
Yet again.

1111
01:26:54,790 --> 01:26:57,150
We're gonna really have to tackle
a lot better than the English are.

1112
01:26:57,200 --> 01:26:58,500
- Yeah. That's sure.
- That's sure.

1113
01:26:58,550 --> 01:26:59,800
- We do.
- Ja.

1114
01:26:59,940 --> 01:27:02,540
<i>That is Lomu's second try this
afternoon.</i>

1115
01:27:03,040 --> 01:27:06,060
<i>This guy really likes scoring tries
against the English...</i>

1116
01:27:06,110 --> 01:27:09,410
Are those the judicial appointments
for the Free State?

1117
01:27:09,820 --> 01:27:12,500
They'll keep until after the match.

1118
01:27:14,860 --> 01:27:16,310
<i>Here's the kick.</i>

1119
01:27:17,280 --> 01:27:19,280
I'm the President, you know.

1120
01:27:20,680 --> 01:27:23,020
<i>And the conversion is good!</i>

1121
01:27:24,120 --> 01:27:27,540
Are you watching this guy?
He's about your size, but...

1122
01:27:27,590 --> 01:27:29,840
How much does this Lomu weigh?

1123
01:27:29,980 --> 01:27:31,880
- 120 kilos.
- Shit.

1124
01:27:32,230 --> 01:27:35,380
- Same as me.
- Yeah., but you're slow.

1125
01:27:38,050 --> 01:27:40,430
Lomu looks for contact every time
he gets the ball.

1126
01:27:40,480 --> 01:27:41,190
Ja.

1127
01:27:41,240 --> 01:27:42,250
It's good for us.

1128
01:27:42,300 --> 01:27:43,110
Ja.

1129
01:27:43,220 --> 01:27:46,380
I will break my arm,
my leg, my neck,

1130
01:27:46,970 --> 01:27:48,650
but I will not let that frickin' guy
go.

1131
01:27:48,700 --> 01:27:49,900
With you, cappie.

1132
01:27:49,950 --> 01:27:53,000
- With you, captain.
- With you, cappie. With you.

1133
01:27:59,320 --> 01:28:01,770
...when you pass it, yeah? Grab this.

1134
01:28:07,020 --> 01:28:08,040
Run!

1135
01:28:08,410 --> 01:28:09,380
Yes.

1136
01:28:14,240 --> 01:28:17,140
Still think I'm wasting my time with
the rugby?

1137
01:28:24,420 --> 01:28:26,420
<i>...he's in the clear and he will...</i>

1138
01:28:26,470 --> 01:28:30,070
Brenda, please tell the Minister
of Sport

1139
01:28:30,270 --> 01:28:33,160
I'd like the full report on
the All Blacks.

1140
01:28:34,510 --> 01:28:37,940
This rugby, it's still strictly
political?

1141
01:28:37,990 --> 01:28:39,890
Oh yes. Oh yes. Of course.

1142
01:28:48,660 --> 01:28:50,260
Hello, Francois.

1143
01:28:54,880 --> 01:28:56,810
Don't lose them. I won't be able
to get more.

1144
01:28:56,860 --> 01:28:58,310
Thanks, Francois.

1145
01:28:59,090 --> 01:29:02,190
Me, mom, Nerine--- wait,

1146
01:29:02,870 --> 01:29:04,220
and the fourth?

1147
01:29:04,490 --> 01:29:05,740
Who's it for?

1148
01:29:24,580 --> 01:29:27,790
The All Blacks beat Ireland 43 to 19.

1149
01:29:28,270 --> 01:29:29,240
I see.

1150
01:29:29,320 --> 01:29:31,550
They beat Wales 34 to 9.

1151
01:29:32,060 --> 01:29:32,960
I see.

1152
01:29:33,020 --> 01:29:36,270
They beat Japan 145 to 17.

1153
01:29:37,040 --> 01:29:40,010
145 points, in one match?

1154
01:29:40,340 --> 01:29:42,540
It's a new international record.

1155
01:29:43,330 --> 01:29:46,430
They beat Scotland 48 to 30 in the
quarter finals.

1156
01:29:46,950 --> 01:29:48,670
You saw the match with England.

1157
01:29:48,720 --> 01:29:49,590
Yes.

1158
01:29:50,550 --> 01:29:54,190
45 to 29. And it was not that close.

1159
01:29:56,050 --> 01:29:58,080
They seem unstoppable.

1160
01:29:58,440 --> 01:30:02,860
If the opposing teams play them
straight up, Jonah Lomu runs wild.

1161
01:30:03,050 --> 01:30:05,960
If they focus on Lomu, that leaves
others free.

1162
01:30:06,210 --> 01:30:08,960
And, also, there's the business of
the haka.

1163
01:30:09,040 --> 01:30:10,990
A Maori war dance. Yes.

1164
01:30:11,690 --> 01:30:13,240
It's very powerful.

1165
01:30:16,080 --> 01:30:18,550
My sources tell me that half of the
All Black matches

1166
01:30:18,600 --> 01:30:21,550
are won before the first whistle,
because of it.

1167
01:30:22,600 --> 01:30:24,250
How can we beat them?

1168
01:30:25,120 --> 01:30:28,720
I have the coach's number.
Maybe, you could call him and ask.

1169
01:30:28,770 --> 01:30:33,710
No. no. I don't want to distract
their focus, even for one minute.

1170
01:30:35,480 --> 01:30:38,120
But, how can we win?

1171
01:30:38,530 --> 01:30:41,610
Maybe we won't. They're favored
two-to-one.

1172
01:30:42,540 --> 01:30:46,730
Madiba, we've already exceeded all
expectations. On and off the field.

1173
01:30:47,490 --> 01:30:51,520
It's not enough. Not now.
Not so close.

1174
01:30:53,570 --> 01:30:56,890
This country is hungry for greatness.

1175
01:31:17,440 --> 01:31:20,140
I brought one of your mom's protein
shakes.

1176
01:31:25,540 --> 01:31:27,340
Thinking about tomorrow?

1177
01:31:28,180 --> 01:31:28,930
No,

1178
01:31:30,240 --> 01:31:32,090
tomorrow's taken care of,

1179
01:31:33,090 --> 01:31:34,640
one way or another.

1180
01:31:36,720 --> 01:31:41,050
I'm was thinking about how you
spend 30 years in a tiny cell,

1181
01:31:43,760 --> 01:31:47,260
and come out ready to forgive
the people who put you there.

1182
01:31:55,570 --> 01:31:58,720
Go home, man. There's nothing more
you can do today.

1183
01:32:03,270 --> 01:32:06,170
Have I ever mentioned to you that
I hate rugby?

1184
01:32:06,380 --> 01:32:08,450
Once or twice, yes.

1185
01:32:11,240 --> 01:32:14,190
I just want to get him through
tomorrow, safely.

1186
01:32:14,690 --> 01:32:15,840
That's all.

1187
01:32:16,350 --> 01:32:17,450
We all do.

1188
01:32:44,310 --> 01:32:47,710
The tickets sold out long before
the team became popular.

1189
01:32:48,300 --> 01:32:52,090
it's not exactly going to be the
rainbow nation out there.

1190
01:32:53,080 --> 01:32:54,830
And that's the reality.

1191
01:32:55,460 --> 01:33:00,180
Now, all it takes is one idiot
trying to make a statement,

1192
01:33:01,050 --> 01:33:05,350
or one fool who thinks that he hears
god speaking to him through the radio.

1193
01:33:06,320 --> 01:33:07,970
It's happened before!

1194
01:33:08,160 --> 01:33:09,660
But not today.

1195
01:33:10,240 --> 01:33:11,690
Not on our watch.

1196
01:33:11,950 --> 01:33:13,450
And not today.

1197
01:33:54,260 --> 01:33:56,130
Hey. Flag face. Flag face.

1198
01:33:56,180 --> 01:33:58,030
- Flag face?
- Bugger off!

1199
01:34:04,280 --> 01:34:07,070
We're at Ellis Park on this historic
day,

1200
01:34:07,170 --> 01:34:12,300
where, even this early, crowd
expectation is at fever pitch...

1201
01:34:13,050 --> 01:34:16,100
<i>because their beloved green and gold</i>

1202
01:34:16,170 --> 01:34:19,920
<i>have somehow managed to defy all
expectations.</i>

1203
01:34:20,160 --> 01:34:25,030
<i>But now they come up against a team
unlike any they have played before.</i>

1204
01:34:25,680 --> 01:34:30,790
<i>These All Blacks are possibly one of
the greatest international sides ever,</i>

1205
01:34:30,940 --> 01:34:35,405
<i>with a player in Jonah Lomu
who is as dominant as any</i>

1206
01:34:35,640 --> 01:34:37,890
<i>this correspondent has ever seen.</i>

1207
01:34:50,590 --> 01:34:52,030
Madiba!

1208
01:35:44,330 --> 01:35:46,130
Final approach, Captain.

1209
01:35:47,940 --> 01:35:51,280
Let it be noted that I'm taking
control of the aircraft.

1210
01:35:51,330 --> 01:35:52,830
Duly noted.

1211
01:35:54,100 --> 01:35:57,450
I take full responsibility for what
happens from now on.

1212
01:36:18,000 --> 01:36:20,250
Do you see that jet, to the east?

1213
01:36:22,440 --> 01:36:23,920
<i>Did they get clearance for this?</i>

1214
01:36:23,970 --> 01:36:25,470
Not from us.

1215
01:36:28,380 --> 01:36:29,740
Where is he?

1216
01:36:29,960 --> 01:36:31,460
<i>VIP box.</i>

1217
01:36:31,800 --> 01:36:33,700
Get him out of there. Now.

1218
01:36:34,090 --> 01:36:35,590
No time.

1219
01:37:01,210 --> 01:37:02,960
What the hell was that?

1220
01:37:44,880 --> 01:37:46,380
- Boka!
- Yeah.

1221
01:37:47,830 --> 01:37:49,330
Come on!

1222
01:38:25,180 --> 01:38:28,960
<i>...World Cup Finals.</i>

1223
01:38:43,440 --> 01:38:47,330
<i>Please welcome the South African
Springboks!</i>

1224
01:39:01,440 --> 01:39:03,860
<i>And New Zealand; All blacks.</i>

1225
01:39:42,510 --> 01:39:44,850
<i>Ladies and gentlemen, please welcome</i>

1226
01:39:44,900 --> 01:39:48,060
<i>The President of the Republic of
South Africa</i>

1227
01:39:48,380 --> 01:39:51,260
<i>Mr. Nelson Mandela.</i>

1228
01:40:01,180 --> 01:40:03,730
<i>Dr. Nelson Mandela, the President of
South Africa</i>

1229
01:40:03,780 --> 01:40:07,030
<i>in the rugby jersey with the number
six on its back...</i>

1230
01:40:07,810 --> 01:40:09,860
The All Black's won't like it.

1231
01:40:11,900 --> 01:40:15,320
Francois, your country is very
proud of you.

1232
01:40:15,950 --> 01:40:17,000
Thank you, sir.

1233
01:40:17,050 --> 01:40:18,860
- Good luck.
- Thank you.

1234
01:40:19,580 --> 01:40:22,000
- ...Mr. President.
- Mr. President. Thank you.

1235
01:40:22,050 --> 01:40:23,800
Good luck to you, son.

1236
01:40:24,830 --> 01:40:26,580
Good luck to you, son.

1237
01:40:31,190 --> 01:40:33,840
<i>Both teams are out there with
Dr. Mandela.</i>

1238
01:40:34,580 --> 01:40:39,660
Chester, I want you to know that
your whole country is supporting you.

1239
01:40:39,930 --> 01:40:42,030
- Good luck.
- Thank  you, sir.

1240
01:40:42,910 --> 01:40:44,230
- Good luck, son.
- Thank you.

1241
01:40:44,280 --> 01:40:46,160
<i>What a dramatic moment here in
Ellis park.</i>

1242
01:40:46,210 --> 01:40:49,660
<i>I don't think I've ever seen so many
flags in one stadium.</i>

1243
01:40:58,970 --> 01:41:00,620
- Hi.
- Their captain.

1244
01:41:00,850 --> 01:41:02,300
I'm honored, sir.

1245
01:41:05,780 --> 01:41:07,360
Mr. President...

1246
01:41:07,410 --> 01:41:09,280
- Yonah?
- Yes. Jonah, sir.

1247
01:41:09,330 --> 01:41:10,880
- Nice to see you.
- Yes. Thank you.

1248
01:41:10,930 --> 01:41:12,880
I'm a little afraid of you.

1249
01:41:13,140 --> 01:41:15,090
<i>...and that's big Jonah Lomu.</i>

1250
01:41:15,140 --> 01:41:16,640
<i>A big day for him.</i>

1251
01:41:18,850 --> 01:41:20,960
- We're all together now.
- Yes.

1252
01:41:21,010 --> 01:41:22,110
Good luck.

1253
01:41:23,650 --> 01:41:26,220
"Nelson... Nelson... Nelson..."

1254
01:41:27,920 --> 01:41:30,240
"NELSON... NELSON... NELSON..."

1255
01:41:35,100 --> 01:41:39,620
<i>...Dr. Mandela just lifting his cap
to the sixty-two thousand people....</i>

1256
01:41:39,680 --> 01:41:42,310
"Nelson... Nelson... Nelson..."

1257
01:41:55,523 --> 01:41:58,071
...wonderful aerial shot of...

1258
01:41:58,510 --> 01:42:00,310
<i>...Ellis Park Stadium...</i>

1259
01:42:04,480 --> 01:42:07,340
<i>Very emotional moment for both
teams.</i>

1260
01:42:26,060 --> 01:42:30,160
<i>Ladies and gentlemen, the national
anthem of South Africa.</i>

1261
01:42:32,050 --> 01:42:34,200
<i>South African National Anthems.</i>

1262
01:43:05,450 --> 01:43:08,700
<i>What an unbelievable spectacular
year in Johannesburg.</i>

1263
01:44:21,930 --> 01:44:24,630
Perhaps we should make a little
wager.

